<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-175] Use IOUtils, FileLineIterable/Iterator across the project</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-175</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The patch I will attach does a couple things:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uses FileLineIterable/Iterator for iterating over lines of a file. This is slightly tidier, but also addresses a few subtle issues across the code base, where reading of files did not always end by closing the stream, or, relied on platform default character encoding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uses IOUtils consistently to close Closeables, swallowing and logging exceptions in cases where they are not to be treated as errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally, fixes some issues in ARFFIterator while I&apos;m at it &amp;#8211; hasNext() changes state, when next() should, and next() did not throw NoSuchElementException&lt;/p&gt;</description>
